&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; I remember the controversy and some real evidence of harm to users &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; and businesses in 2020 when we partitioned the HTTP cache, but I was &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; convinced that we had to accept that harm in order to credibly achieve &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; 3PCD. At the time I was personally a fan of a proposal like this (even &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; for &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; users without 3PCs) in order to mitigate the harm. But now it seems to &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; me &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; that if we're going to start talking about poking holes in that &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; decision, &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; perhaps we should be doing a larger review of the options in that space &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; with the knowledge that most Chrome users are likely to continue to &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; have 3PCs enabled. WDYT? &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Thanks, &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Rick &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; On Mon, Oct 27, 2025 at 10:27 AM Patrick Meenan &lt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; &lt;a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection" class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="3c4c51591212127c5f544e535155495112534e5b"&gt;[email&#160;protected]&lt;/a&gt;&gt; wrote: &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; I don't believe the security/privacy protections actually rely on &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; the assertions (and it's unlikely those would be public). It's more for &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; awareness and to make sure they don't accidentally break something with &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt