&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p class="darkgray font13"&gt;
&lt;span class="sender pipe"&gt;&lt;a href="/search?l=blink-dev@chromium.org&amp;q=from:%22%27Nathan+Memmott%27+via+blink%5C-dev%22" rel="nofollow"&gt;&lt;span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person"&gt;&lt;span itemprop="name"&gt;'Nathan Memmott' via blink-dev&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="date"&gt;&lt;a href="/search?l=blink-dev@chromium.org&amp;q=date:20251203" rel="nofollow"&gt;Wed, 03 Dec 2025 11:37:59 -0800&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div itemprop="articleBody" class="msgBody"&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;Hi all,

Per this discussion
&lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://github.com/webmachinelearning/writing-assistance-apis/issues/83"&gt;https://github.com/webmachinelearning/writing-assistance-apis/issues/83&lt;/a&gt;&gt;,
we're relaxing the user activation requirements for Writer, Rewriter,
Summarizer &lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://github.com/webmachinelearning/writing-assistance-apis"&gt;https://github.com/webmachinelearning/writing-assistance-apis&lt;/a&gt;&gt;,
Proofreader &lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://github.com/webmachinelearning/proofreader-api"&gt;https://github.com/webmachinelearning/proofreader-api&lt;/a&gt;&gt;, and
Prompt &lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://github.com/webmachinelearning/prompt-api"&gt;https://github.com/webmachinelearning/prompt-api&lt;/a&gt;&gt; APIs. Currently
when a model is &quot;downloadable&quot;
&lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://webmachinelearning.github.io/writing-assistance-apis/#dom-availability-downloadable"&gt;https://webmachinelearning.github.io/writing-assistance-apis/#dom-availability-downloadable&lt;/a&gt;&gt;,
creating
a session for these APIs consumes transient user activation. We're updating
it so that when the model is &quot;downloadable&quot;, it only requires sticky user
activation. We are making no changes to when the model is &quot;available&quot;
&lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://webmachinelearning.github.io/writing-assistance-apis/#dom-availability-available"&gt;https://webmachinelearning.github.io/writing-assistance-apis/#dom-availability-available&lt;/a&gt;&gt;
and
will continue not to require user activation.&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;pre&gt;

Thanks,
Nathan

